#: ../building_the_car.rst:2
msgid "Building the Car"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:4
msgid "Are you excited when you open the box and see so many components? Keep your patience and take it easy. Please note that some details in the following steps need careful observation. You should double-check your work based on the figures in the manual after finishing each step. let’s start!"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:11
msgid "Front Wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:13
msgid "Insert an **M4x25 screw** through a **Steering Connector Plate**, 3 **Bearing Shields**, 3 **Hex Front Wheel Fixing Plates**, and a **front wheel**, into an **M4 Self-locking Nut** as shown below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:21
msgid "You can use the Cross Socket Wrench to secure the **M4 Self-locking Nut**, then use the screwdriver to tighten the **M4x25 screw.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:29
msgid "The Self-locking Nut should be screwed tight enough. It would be better to tighten the screw until the wheel and Steering Connector cannot move first, then loosen the screw a little, so that the Steering Plate can just move. Thus, the wheel can turn flexibly when the connection would not be too loose."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:35
msgid "Assemble the other front wheel in the same way, but bear in mind the Steering Connector plate on the wheel should be symmetric with the previous one."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:43
msgid "Now two front wheels have finished assembly."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:46
msgid "Pan-and-Tilt"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:48
msgid "Take out the **Cross rocker arm** and mount it onto the **Pan-and-tilt Base Plate** with 2 **M1.5x4 screws** (into the hole like this). Pay attention to the holes on the round rocker arm to be fastened."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:55
msgid "Do the same operation to the **Camera Mount Plate**."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:60
msgid "Assemble the two servos to the **Pan-and-tilt Plate** with four **M2x8 screws** and the **M2 nuts** (The 2 servo shaft are close to the left side ):"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:69
msgid "Steering Part"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:71
msgid "Connect the **Steering Linkage** and the **1-arm Rocker Arm** with the **M1.5x4 Self-tapping Screw**."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:75
msgid "Insert it into the **FIRST** hole of the arm (as indicated by the **arrow** below) which is the farthest from the gears."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:81
msgid "And also fasten them as tightly as possible, and then loosen the screw a little so the Steering Linkage can move flexibly."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:85
msgid "Upper Plate"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:87
msgid "Mount the **M2.5x8 copper standoffs** and **M2.5 nuts** into the **upper plate** first. Pay attention that the side the protruding prop should face up."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:95
msgid "Battery Holder"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:97
msgid "Turn the Upper Plate upside down. Cut the **ribbon** into two halves. Thread them through the holes on the plate. Pay attention to the direction and leave one end longer out of the plate for each to remove the battery easily later."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:105
msgid "Fasten the battery holder with two **M3x8 countersunk screws** and **M3 nuts**. Pay attention to the direction of battery holder’s wire."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:112
msgid "Rear Wheels (Screws)"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:114
msgid "Insert 4 **M3x8 screws** with four **M3x25 copper standoffs**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:120
msgid "PCB Assembly"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:122
msgid "Assemble the **Raspberry Pi** (TF Card inserted) with 8 **M2.5x8 single pass** **copper standoffs**, then plug the **Robot HATS** onto it."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:126
msgid "Fix the **Robot HATS** with 4 **M2.5x6** **screws**."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:128
msgid "3) Fix The **PCA9685 PWM Driver** and the **Motor Driver** with 8 **M2.5x12** **screws and M2.5 nuts** into the **down plate：**"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:135
msgid "Fixing Rear Wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:137
msgid "Assemble the two motors with four **M3x25 screws** and **M3 nuts**. Pay attention to place the motors with wires inward, providing convenience for connecting the circuit."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:144
msgid "Assemble the rear wheels with 4 M3 nuts."
msgstr ""

#: ../building_the_car.rst:149
msgid "Align the **rear** **wheels** with the motor shaft, and rotate to insert them gently."
msgstr ""
